  "prompt": "Where should I register my domain name in Singapore?",
  "response": "In Singapore, there are several reputable registrars where you can register your domain name. Here are some popular options:\n\n1. **SGNIC (Singapore Network Information Centre)**: SGNIC is the official registry for .sg domain names. You can find a list of accredited registrars on their website.\n\n2. **Domain.com.sg**: This is a local registrar that offers .sg and other domain extensions, along with additional services like web hosting and email.\n\n3. **Exabytes**: A well-known web hosting company in Singapore that also provides domain registration services.\n\n4. **Vodien**: Another popular web hosting provider that also offers domain registration, website development, and other online services.\n\n5. **Hostinger**: They provide domain registration services along with affordable web hosting solutions.\n\n6. **GoDaddy**: A global registrar that allows you to register various domain extensions, including .sg, although they may charge a higher fee for local domains.\n\n7. **Bluehost**: While primarily a web hosting provider, Bluehost also offers domain registration services.\n\nWhen choosing a registrar, consider factors such as pricing, customer support, ease of use, and any additional services you may need, like web hosting or email services. Always ensure that the registrar is accredited by SGNIC if you're looking to register a .sg domain.",
